hands_on_practices.solution:
We use the Landau criterion for the onset of spontaneous emission by a heavy impurity ($M\to\infty$), which neglects recoil.  The critical velocity $v_c$ is given by
$$
v_c \;=\;\min_{\vec q}\frac{\omega_{\vec q}}{|\vec q|}
\;=\;\min_{q>0}\frac{\Delta+\frac{\hbar^2q^2}{2m}}{q}\,.
$$
Define the function
$$
f(q)=\frac{\Delta}{q}+\frac{\hbar^2 q}{2m}\,.
$$
1.  Compute the derivative and set to zero:
$$
f'(q)=-\frac{\Delta}{q^2}+\frac{\hbar^2}{2m}=0
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\frac{\hbar^2}{2m}=\frac{\Delta}{q^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
q^2=\frac{2m\Delta}{\hbar^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
q_0=\frac{\sqrt{2m\Delta}}{\hbar}\,.
$$
2.  Evaluate $f(q)$ at $q_0$:
$$
f(q_0)
=\frac{\Delta}{q_0}+\frac{\hbar^2q_0}{2m}
=\frac{\Delta}{\sqrt{2m\Delta}/\hbar}
+\frac{\hbar^2}{2m}\,\frac{\sqrt{2m\Delta}}{\hbar}
=\hbar\,\frac{\sqrt{\Delta}}{\sqrt{2m}}
+\hbar\,\frac{\sqrt{\Delta}}{\sqrt{2m}}
=2\hbar\,\frac{\sqrt{\Delta}}{\sqrt{2m}}
=\hbar\sqrt{\frac{2\Delta}{m}}\,.
$$
Therefore the critical velocity is
$$
v_c=\hbar\sqrt{\frac{2\Delta}{m}}\,.
$$

1. First-order energy shift (mean‐field):
$$\Delta E^{(1)}=n_0\,G=n_0\bigl(g_{IB}-i\tfrac{\eta}{2}\bigr).$$

2. Second-order energy shift (heavy impurity, no recoil):
Converting the sum over virtual modes to an integral with cutoff $q_c$, the second-order shift for the non-Hermitian interaction is:
$$\Delta E^{(2)}=-n_0\,G^2\int^{q_c}\frac{d^3q}{(2\pi)^3}\frac{\epsilon_q}{(\hbar\omega_q)^2}.$$

3. Phonon approximation: $\hbar\omega_q\approx c_s\hbar q$, $\epsilon_q=\frac{\hbar^2q^2}{2m_B}$. Hence
$$\frac{\epsilon_q}{(\hbar\omega_q)^2}
=\frac{\hbar^2q^2/(2m_B)}{(c_s^2\hbar^2q^2)}
=\frac1{2m_Bc_s^2}
=\frac1{2\,g_{BB}n_0},$$
using $c_s^2=g_{BB}n_0/m_B$.

4. Perform the momentum integral:
$$\int^{q_c}\frac{d^3q}{(2\pi)^3}
=\frac{4\pi q_c^3/3}{(2\pi)^3}
=\frac{q_c^3}{6\pi^2}.$$
Thus
$$\Delta E^{(2)}
=-n_0\,G^2\frac1{2g_{BB}n_0}\frac{q_c^3}{6\pi^2}
=-\frac{G^2\,q_c^3}{12\pi^2\,g_{BB}}.$$

5. Total energy shift up to second order:
$$\Delta E_{pol}=\Delta E^{(1)}+\Delta E^{(2)}
=n_0G-\frac{G^2\,q_c^3}{12\pi^2\,g_{BB}}.$$

6. Extract imaginary part. Write $G=g_{IB}-i\frac{\eta}{2}$ so
$$\Im\,\Delta E_{pol}
=-\frac{\eta n_0}{2}-\Im\!\bigl(G^2\bigr)\frac{q_c^3}{12\pi^2\,g_{BB}},
\quad
\Im(G^2)=-g_{IB}\,\eta.$$
Therefore
$$\Im\,\Delta E_{pol}
=-\frac{\eta n_0}{2}+\frac{g_{IB}\,\eta\,q_c^3}{12\pi^2\,g_{BB}}.$$

7. Loss rate $\Gamma=-2\,\Im\,\Delta E_{pol}$:
$$\Gamma
=\eta n_0-\frac{g_{IB}\,\eta\,q_c^3}{6\pi^2\,g_{BB}}.$$
